[2] Guatemala (Quetzaltenango)
Date: Thu 21 May 2009
Source: Prensa Libre [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.prensalibre.com/pl/2009/mayo/21/316044.html>


Since April [2009], classical dengue was declared epidemic in Coatepeque,
due to 50 cases that have been reported, 44 of them from various
neighborhoods of the city. Juan Esau de Leon, coordinator of the Vectors
Section of the health area, commented that 44 [dengue] cases have been
reported thus far in May [2009]. Most of the people affected are from the
neighborhoods of Las Casas, 8 cases, La Esperanza y El Rosario, with 5
each, and in rural areas 6 cases have been reported.

[byline: Edgar Octavio Giron]

