[4] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Mon 18 May 2009
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/cidades/mat/2009/05/18/casos-de-dengue-notificados-na-bahia-chegam-69-mil-51-ja-morreram-este-ano-755915029.asp>


[The number of] dengue cases in Bahia have reached 69 000; 51 have died
this year [2009]. The state Secretariat of Health of Bahia issued a
bulletin this Monday [18 May 2009] about dengue [cases] recorded in the
state this year [2009]. From the beginning of 2009 until 9 May [2009],
there have been 68 959 recorded dengue cases in 366 Bahia municipalities.
This number is 173 per cent higher that that registered for the same period
last year [2008]. In total, 51 people have died, victims of the disease, 27
or whom were less than 15 years of age.

According to the Secretariat, the municipalities of Itabuna, Jequie,
Ilheus, Porto Seguro, Salvador, and Feira de Santana had 50 per cent of the
recorded cases. An additional 526 serious cases of the illness were
recorded in 99 cities of the state.

